<subSubSection id="44C472C38647C35528D2A33F1471F8E3" pageId="13" pageNumber="470" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="0C6121488647C35528D2A33F1471F8E3" blockId="13.[173,1380,876,1850]" pageId="13" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="3EAAFD5A8647C35528D2A33F1259F96E" bold="true" box="[175,519,1659,1692]" pageId="13" pageNumber="470">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Least Concern on The [UCN Red List. The region where the Rio Jurua Collared Titi occurs is isolated and suffers little anthropogenic impact. It is found in Rio Bia and Vale do Javari indigenous reservations and may also occur in Jutai-Solimoes Ecological Reserve.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
